How odd. slime god (guy below me) is dead on. Writing quality? Great.The subtle pull at what you focus on is pretty nice. Usually, is all about looking good and getting you off, so a difference is nice to have.
Morally? Disgusting, but with a dash of wholesome(?). The obsession isn't a good thing for anyone involved. She might have permanent scars from this, and he banks his existence as a human in the eyes of society on his child (Since rapists deserve death.) The mother might kill him, too. Decent fap, though. Got me questioning my morals a bit, which is good to do, sometimes

Part2) So the fact that the author directly confronts how fucked up it all is, right in front of the reader, is amazing. It becomes harder to dismiss the reality of the situation, and honestly might force some readers to forget what they saw to resume suspension of disbelief… or put themselves in the father’s shoes and see where that takes them. The themes and concepts I think the author intended to shift our focus to were really well laid out through dialogue. Part of what I really liked was this subtle feeling that the dad knows that this cannot last - and how we observe his growing attachment (borderline obsession) with his daughter, which was born purely in spite of his wife cheating on him, turning to the one person who relied on him unconditionally for their whole life. A fascinating amount of depth packed into a short amount of pages, I’m a big fan. Also it made me nut. 9/10.

Part1) I don’t really see page 11 the same way. I gathered it as the father questioning the morality of what he was doing. With how (somehow) realistic a lot of the plot points are, the connection between father and daughter have course to be so strong - obviously not to the point of incest, but here we are of course.

The father sees that the person before him is completely defenseless and innocent in that moment - just as she was when he was changing her diapers. I don’t think that was for the reader to find as arousing - I almost found it as an indicator to shift the reader’s attention to the themes and circumstances, rather than the purely visual aspect.

The abstract concept of incest that I enjoy in reading is the mere concept of two individuals so incredibly close and spiritually connected, they are willing to throw away everything to experience eachother’s love. It’s the CONCEPT of incest that I find so arousing, not so much the practice and what it really is… in REALITY.
